{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the current fossil record itself represents a limited and imbalanced selection of specimens-essentially a series of snapshots that cover only a small fraction of the overall historical biodiversity, at highly varied levels of preservation.",
    "These factors complicate efforts to standardize model evaluation and to draw definitive conclusions about methodological efficacy.",
    "To chart the evolution of fossil classification and segmentation DL methods, we have included a figure that chronologically maps out the studies included herein from each field.",
    "Figure 9 categorizes the studies based on their methodological approaches and displays the corresponding references for each.",
    "This visual representation provides a chronological overview of the research landscape, highlighting the progression of different approaches over time and helping to contextualize the trends discussed."
  ]
}